\ Sort/unique correctness, stability, fast-path, and fallback regressions.

'check [ [ ] [ "sort/unique check failed" error ] ifelse ] def

[] sort [] == check
( ) sort ( ) == check
"" sort "" == check
[ 3 1 2 ] sort [ 1 2 3 ] == check
( "c" "a" "b" ) sort ( "a" "b" "c" ) == check
"cba" sort "abc" == check

\ Mixed numerics compare by value and equal values retain input order.
[ 1.0 1 0 ] sort [ 0 1.0 1 ] == check
[ 3 1.5 2 ] sort [ 1.5 2 3 ] == check

0 512 range reverse sort 0 512 range == check
0 128 range reverse >list sort 0 128 range >list == check

\ Exercise the byte-counting path without embedding a large expected string.
"" 8 [ "zyxwvutsrqponmlkjihgfedcba" concat ] times sort
dup len 208 == check
dup "a" indexof 0 == check
dup "b" indexof 8 == check
dup "z" indexof 200 == check
last "z" == check

[ [ true ] sort ] [ "unsupported-sort" ] try "unsupported-sort" == check
[ [ 1 "x" ] sort ] [ "mixed-sort" ] try "mixed-sort" == check
[ 0 3 range 1 nan set-at sort ] [ "nan-sort" ] try "nan-sort" == check

[] unique [] == check
"banana" unique "ban" == check
[ 1 2 1 3 2 ] unique [ 1 2 3 ] == check
( 1 2 1 3 2 ) unique ( 1 2 3 ) == check
[ 1 "a" 1 "a" 'x 'x ] unique [ 1 "a" 'x ] == check
[ 1.0 1.0 2.0 ] unique [ 1.0 2.0 ] == check
[ [ 1 ] [ 1 ] [ 2 ] ] unique [ [ 1 ] [ 2 ] ] == check

0 128 range unique 0 128 range == check
0 128 range [ 16 % ] map unique 0 16 range == check
0 128 range [ 16 % ] map >list unique 0 16 range >list == check

\ Equality says NaN is unequal to itself, so unique retains both occurrences.
[] nan push-back nan push-back unique len 2 == check
